{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb559337b-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s742"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"742"},"text":"§ 742.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" National preparedness","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In order to prepare the Nation for all hazards, including natural disasters, acts of terrorism, and other man-made disasters, the President, consistent with the declaration of policy under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5195"},"text":"section 5195 of title 42","children":[],"tail":" and title V of the Homeland Security Act of 2002 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s311"},"text":"6 U.S.C. 311","children":[],"tail":" et seq.), as amended by this Act, shall develop a national preparedness goal and a national preparedness system."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb559337c-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/295/tVI/s642"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–295, title VI, § 642","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-04"},"text":"Oct. 4, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/1425"},"text":"120 Stat. 1425","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb559337d-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb559337e-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb559337f-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Homeland Security Act of 2002, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–296","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2135"},"text":"116 Stat. 2135","children":[],"tail":". Title V of the Act is classified generally to subchapter V (§ 311 et seq.) of chapter 1 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This Act, referred to in text, means title VI of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/295"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–295","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-04"},"text":"Oct. 4, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/1394"},"text":"120 Stat. 1394","children":[],"tail":", known as the Post-Katrina Emergency Management Reform Act of 2006. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title and References in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/295"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–295","children":[],"tail":" notes set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s701"},"text":"section 701 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
